Playing some shows with @badbloomny at the end of the month. See you there?

Super Dark Collective Presents Creeks (Jon Simmons of Balance and Composure), Bad Bloom, A Cave In Bloom & Stroma on January 27th. Vibe - Shoegaze / Post-Punk / Dream Pop.

Tickets on sale NOW at nofuntroy dot eventbrite dot com. $10 ADV / $15 Door. No Fun 275 River Troy.

More about the show:

Creeks - Even though Balance & Composure have broken up, Jon Simmons never stopped writing. On his second record as a solo artist under the moniker CREEKS, Simmons strips everything back to the bare essentials, a guitar and his voice. “The Pain You Took On” was reissued on vinyl via Born Losers Records.

Bad Bloom - In late 2019, Bad Bloom was created in Queens, New York. The band recorded a three-song EP, ‘Candle’, inspired by shoegaze and dreampop legends Ride, DIIV, My Bloody Valentine with Post-Punk and Indie influencers such as The Cure, Talking Heads, Rainer Maria, & Jenny Lewis. Seeking a change of pace, Bad Bloom left NYC, moved to Rochester, NY. With a new line up and new sound, they are currently recording and plan to release in 2023, along with playing across the US.

Local support by new capital region acts A Cave In Bloom & Stroma. Going to be a rad winter gig. Come through!
